DOC.brief_summary: The aim of the study is to evaluate and compare the effects of high-intensity (deadlift) versus low-intensity motor control exercises on selfrated pain, function and symptoms on patients with peripherally mediated pain
DOC.brief_title: High(Deadlift) Versus Low Intensity Motor Control Exercises on Low Back Pain
DOC.criteria: low back pain over 3 month the pain must originate locally from the lowe back and be nociceptive
